Performers celebrate the Chinese New Year in Macao on February 3, 2022. Photo: ICAn online get-together party to celebrate China's Spring Festival, which fell on February 1, 2022 was held in Malta on Sunday evening.The gala was jointly organized by the China Cultural Center in Malta, the Confucius Institute of the University of Malta, the 17th China medical team for Malta and the Center for Traditional Chinese Medicine of the University of Malta.Maltese people were also invited to participate in the online party, which featured a variety of activities including artistic performances, a knowledge quiz and interactive experiences.Artistic performances such as the chorus of "When smiling you are very nice,"Â  talk show "Chinese Zodiac" and "Traditional Chinese medicine culture" brought joy to the audience. Several Maltese students learning the Chinese at the China Cultural Center also sang their favorite songs.A knowledge quiz about Chinese culture and the Olympic Winter Games was also held, coupled with a short video showing winter tourism in North China.At the height of the online gathering, Chinese and Maltese audiences learned to sing "Together for a Shared Future" and greeted "Happy New Year" in Chinese, Maltese and English.This was the second year the "Happy Chinese New Year" party was held online due to the pandemic, said Yang Xiaolong, director of the China Cultural Center.